challenge with having a friend

00:01:49.510 --> 00:01:51.790
pick up an iPhone and say like,
hey Jussi, you really

00:01:51.790 --> 00:01:55.280
got to play this game, is that I
actually need to meet you in

00:01:55.280 --> 00:01:57.250
order to see that.

00:01:57.250 --> 00:01:59.980
So Everyplay is really about
taking that moment, oh gee,

00:01:59.980 --> 00:02:01.040
this game rocks.

00:02:01.040 --> 00:02:02.070
I want to show everyone.

00:02:02.070 --> 00:02:03.890
Or I'm doing so well
in this game.

00:02:03.890 --> 00:02:04.990
Look at me.

00:02:04.990 --> 00:02:07.470
And taking that moment and
making it shareable

00:02:07.470 --> 00:02:09.050
by posting it online.

00:02:09.050 --> 00:02:10.539
So that's what Everyplay
really is.

00:02:10.539 --> 00:02:14.140
It's about digitizing word of
mouth and making it shareable.

00:02:14.140 --> 00:02:16.400
JAREK WILKIEWICZ: So
traditionally, this type of

00:02:16.400 --> 00:02:19.950
sharing use case has already
been done in console

00:02:19.950 --> 00:02:21.900
games and PC games.

00:02:21.900 --> 00:02:23.930
We have a lot of that type
of content on YouTube.

00:02:23.930 --> 00:02:25.170
It's extremely popular.

00:02:25.170 --> 00:02:27.610
So how is mobile different?

00:02:27.610 --> 00:02:29.730
JUSSI LAAKKONEN: Mobile
is different in a

00:02:29.730 --> 00:02:31.530
good number of ways.

00:02:31.530 --> 00:02:34.950
First of all, these devices are
considerably lower power

00:02:34.950 --> 00:02:37.676
than your average high-end
PC gaming rig.

00:02:37.676 --> 00:02:40.900
On a PC, you have quite a lot
of horsepower to spare for

00:02:40.900 --> 00:02:42.170
video recording.

00:02:42.170 --> 00:02:44.350
Whereas on a mobile device, it's
actually a pretty hard

00:02:44.350 --> 00:02:47.440
engineering problem to
make it go fast.

00:02:47.440 --> 00:02:51.280
Also what's very different from
PC is that on a PC you

00:02:51.280 --> 00:02:55.150
can actually download a separate
software, like Fraps,

00:02:55.150 --> 00:02:58.300
to record another software.

00:02:58.300 --> 00:03:00.450
Whereas on an iOS
and Android, the

00:03:00.450 --> 00:03:02.710
applications are sandboxed.

00:03:02.710 --> 00:03:05.720
What this means is that another
application cannot

00:03:05.720 --> 00:03:08.790
access the contents of
another application.

00:03:08.790 --> 00:03:10.830
So you actually cannot have
a general purpose

00:03:10.830 --> 00:03:13.200
screen casting tool.

00:03:13.200 --> 00:03:17.800
Instead, what we do is we
provide an SDK that's easily

00:03:17.800 --> 00:03:20.870
integrated into the games and
provides a seamless instant

00:03:20.870 --> 00:03:22.580
replay and sharing solution.

00:03:22.580 --> 00:03:23.020
JAREK WILKIEWICZ: I see.

00:03:23.020 --> 00:03:27.630
So is it fair to say that for
most of the PC titles today,

00:03:27.630 --> 00:03:30.220
the videos that we see on
YouTube are basically captured

00:03:30.220 --> 00:03:33.490
using third party software,
edited locally, and then

00:03:33.490 --> 00:03:34.400
uploaded to YouTube?

00:03:34.400 --> 00:03:38.280
Whereas with mobile, the way
forward is to really

00:03:38.280 --> 00:03:41.524
incorporate this functionality
directly into the game?

00:03:41.524 --> 00:03:43.020
JUSSI LAAKKONEN: That's
absolutely true.

00:03:43.020 --> 00:03:48.500
And it's a function of the
limitations or say

00:03:48.500 --> 00:03:50.910
restrictions and protections
of the iOS and Android

00:03:50.910 --> 00:03:52.400
operating systems.

00:03:52.400 --> 00:03:54.570
And also I think what's
interesting, as you mentioned,

00:03:54.570 --> 00:03:55.630
it's very popular.

00:03:55.630 --> 00:03:57.600
Let's Play videos are
hugely popular.

00:03:57.600 --> 00:04:01.140
And walkthroughs as well as
reviews by user are extremely

00:04:01.140 --> 00:04:02.850
influential on YouTube.

00:04:02.850 --> 00:04:06.740
And what that really speaks to
is that even though making of

00:04:06.740 --> 00:04:09.800
these videos is not trivial, you
need to have the software.

00:04:09.800 --> 00:04:13.170
You need to record and edit
separately and then upload.

00:04:13.170 --> 00:04:15.090
There's a lot of people
doing it.

00:04:15.090 --> 00:04:17.810
And what we are aiming to do for
mobile is to simplify this

00:04:17.810 --> 00:04:22.360
by making it a completely
transparent part of the game.

00:04:22.360 --> 00:04:23.570
So you play the game.

00:04:23.570 --> 00:04:24.460
And you get a replay.

00:04:24.460 --> 00:04:27.420
You don't think about that, oh,
I need a tool for this.

00:04:27.420 --> 00:04:29.030
Or I want to do a replay.

00:04:29.030 --> 00:04:30.140
Instead, you just get it.

00:04:30.140 --> 00:04:33.520
And you can easily share
it or comment on it or

00:04:33.520 --> 00:04:34.380
put it out to YouTube.

00:04:34.380 --> 00:04:37.320
And I think that's really going
to unlock a number of

00:04:37.320 --> 00:04:40.750
creators that would not have
done it on PC because the

00:04:40.750 --> 00:04:43.030
tools were too complicated.

00:04:43.030 --> 00:04:43.400
