00:13:15.230 --> 00:13:18.560
So let's talk a little bit more
about how this system is

00:13:18.560 --> 00:13:19.040
implemented.

00:13:19.040 --> 00:13:20.660
So can you tell us a little
more about the

00:13:20.660 --> 00:13:22.086
technology behind it?

00:13:22.086 --> 00:13:24.020
JUSSI LAAKKONEN: So certainly
there are a couple of

00:13:24.020 --> 00:13:24.800
components with this.

00:13:24.800 --> 00:13:27.600
One is the SDK that goes
inside the game.

00:13:27.600 --> 00:13:34.190
And that's a native iOS code
that we provide in the various

00:13:34.190 --> 00:13:38.600
plug-ins for Unity, Cocoas,
Unreal Engine 3, and custom

00:13:38.600 --> 00:13:39.695
game engines.

00:13:39.695 --> 00:13:42.020
We are also hard at work with
our Android version.

00:13:42.020 --> 00:13:44.550
And we hope to give you news
about that in the not too

00:13:44.550 --> 00:13:45.270
distant future.

00:13:45.270 --> 00:13:46.960
JAREK WILKIEWICZ: That
